research_municipality_step.notes: Plano, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government, which is a variation of the mayor-council system. The City Council consists of the Mayor and seven City Council members, all elected at-large. Candidates for Places 1 through 4 must reside in the corresponding district, while Places 5 through 8 do not have residency restrictions. Place 6 is always the Mayor. The 'Place' designation is used as the division.
